    "costPerLevel": 2,
    "maxLevel": 4,
    "description": "Whether due to inherited racial traits, specialization in a particular type of energy, or inherent extraordinary protection, you are resistant to a specific type of energy. A fiery sorceress immune to the hottest blaze or a biologically anomalous alien race that is immune to poison are both examples of this feat in play.",
    "descriptionHtml": "Whether due to inherited racial traits, specialization in a particular type of energy, or inherent extraordinary protection, you are resistant to a specific type of energy. A fiery sorceress immune to the hottest blaze or a biologically anomalous alien race that is immune to poison are both examples of this feat in play.",
    "effectHtml": "Choose from the following energy types: fire, cold, lightning, acid, poison, or another at the GM's discretion. When you are attacked with that energy type, you gain resistance to the attack as follows:\n\n                                    <ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Tier 1</strong>\n                                            - Your defense scores are increased by 3 against the chosen energy type.\n                                        </li>\n<li>\n<strong>Tier 2</strong>\n                                            - Your defense scores are increased by 6 against the chosen energy type.\n                                        </li>\n<li>\n<strong>Tier 3</strong>\n                                            - Your defense scores are increased by 9 against the chosen energy type.\n                                        </li>\n<li>\n<strong>Tier 4</strong>\n                                            - You are immune to damage and harmful effects from the chosen energy type.\n                                        </li>\n</ul>",
